description.narrative:
The Afghan Mechanism for Inclusive Peace (AMIP) has the objective to contribute to making the Afghan peace process and peace negotiations more inclusive and sustainable;
With the operational objective: to connect discussions and outcomes from track II and III to the negotiations at track I, as well as feeding back information from track I negotiations to track II and III.
AMIP will aim to provide a structured, impartial and non-partisan form of interaction between the tracks I, II and III, and Afghan civil society at large. The mechanism would make sure that critical information and public sentiment analysis on important issues are transferred to the track I negotiators, enabling track II and III and other socio-political cleavages to have their voices heard in the negotiation room. The mechanism will also act as a feedback loop to provide information about the negotiations to the public. This also has the aim of making the peace process more accessible and understandable to the wider Afghan population. The mechanism will be open to receive inputs from all sections of Afghanistan and will serve an impartial, non-partisan and technical function. Gender, ethnic and geographic balance will be kept in mind in make-up of mechanism.
